author: Nathaniel J. Smith
commit_message:
Fix .throw followed immediately by await yield_

This fixes a nasty bug, so that now our YieldWrapper interception is
performed consistently no matter how we re-enter the coroutine
iterator. Before this, it would work so long as we always re-entered via
.send/.__next__, but a .throw() immediately followed by an await
yield_(...)  wouldn't work, and the YieldWrapper object would propagate
back out to the coroutine runner.

author: Nathaniel J. Smith
commit_message:
Slightly simplify AsyncGenerator class

There's no need to allocate a new `ANextIter` object on every call to
`__anext__` -- we can just re-use the same object each time, to slightly
simplify and speed up the code.

Thanks to @bj0 for the suggestion.
